> software development should achieve ROBUSTNESS, ADAPTABILITY AND REUSEABILITY

> the notion of ABSTRACTION is to distill a complicated system down to its fundamental parts

> an ADT(ABSTRACT DATA TYPE) specifies what ech opertion does, but not how it does it

> an iterator for a collection provides one key behaviour. It supports a special method __next__ that returns the next element       	of the collection

> python provides an automatic iterator implementation for any class that defines both __len__ and __getitem__ .

> inheritance represent  as "is a " relationship i.e car is a vehicle

> _ is protected and __ is private similar in python

> there is NO strong tradition of definint abstract base class in python, although python's abc module provides support for defining 	a formal abstract base class
